18: select_related and prefetched_related.

class Author(models.Model):
    name = models.CharField(max_length=100)

class Book(models.Model):
    title = models.CharField(max_length=100)
    author = models.ForeignKey(Author, on_delete=models.CASCADE)


books = Book.objects.select_related('author').all()


select_related() executes a SQL JOIN query to fetch related objects in a single database hit, mainly used for ForeignKey and OneToOne relationships.


prefetch_related() performs separate database queries for related objects and combines them in Python, making it efficient for ManyToMany and reverse ForeignKey relationships using IN queries.



